quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  20,52,"He said, “Knowledge thereof is with my Lord in a record{1}; my Lord never goes astray nor does He forget.”",footnotes:1:Literally ‘scripture’.
  20,53,"<i class=""s"">(He is) </i>the One Who has made the earth a <span class=""h"">cradle<sup foot_note=""80537"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and traced in it ways for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, and sent down from the sky water with which We{2}brought out pairs of diverse plants.",footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from 3rd person to 1st person.
  20,54,"Eat<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and pasture your livestock. Most surely, in that are signs for ones endowed with intelligence."
  20,55,"From it We created you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, and into it We return you, and from it We bring you out once again."
  20,56,"And very truly We showed him all of Our signs, but he disbelieved and refused."
  20,57,"He said, “Have you come to us to evict us from our land with your sorcery, O Moses?"
  20,58,"We will most surely bring you sorcery like it; so make between us and you an appointment which we <span class=""h"">will<sup foot_note=""80539"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">not break</span>—neither us nor you—in a suitable place.”"
  20,59,"He said, “Your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>appointment is the day of the festival, so let the people be herded together at forenoon.”"
  20,60,"Then Pharaoh turned away and put together his plot, and then he came."
  20,61,"Moses said to them, “Woe to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>. Do not fabricate lies against Allah or He will destroy you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>with a punishment, and surely, the one who fabricates lies is bound to fail.”"
  20,62,"Then they disagreed with each other about their matter and conversed secretly."
  20,63,"They said, “<span class=""h"">These two are nothing but<sup foot_note=""80540"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>sorcerers who want to evict you from your land with their sorcery and abolish your exemplary way of life."
  20,64,"So <span class=""h"">decide<sup foot_note=""80541"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>plot, then come, lined up<i class=""s"">(in ranks) </i>; and the one who gains the upper hand is surely bound to succeed today.”"
